 choose how to show your products on the Home page or on the Shop page, with structured descriptions capable of quickly attract your customers’ attention and to make them click on the product to learn more about it.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"YITH Support Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11240:\"    <div class=\"row \">\n		    <div class=\"cols col-lg-9 \">\n		</p>\n<h3>Replace the standard product description with customized and sales-oriented texts</h3>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is the reason why we have designed this plugin: we realised that the plugin description texts on our home page did not faithfully represent what the plugin is, <strong>as the short text used to be taken out of the product detail page automatically</strong>. The loop text used to show a few lines of nonsense text, sometimes even broken sentences.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Looking into our customers’ e-commerce websites made it clear to us that it’s a common issue that any WooCommerce user experiences because almost all of their shops are showing texts that are neither market-oriented nor useful nor informative in any way for the users.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is how we shaped YITH Product Description in Loop: <strong>a simple as well as powerful plugin that generates a textarea on the product detail page</strong>, where you can add (and format) the text that will replace the default one in WooCommerce loop.</p>\n<p>    </div>\n	    <div class=\"cols col-lg-3 \">\n		\n<div class=\"general-features\">\n\n    <h3 class=\"quick-info-title\">Quick info</h3>\n\n    <div class=\"quick-info\">\n\n        <ul class=\"info \">\n			                <li>\n                    <span>Requires:</span>\n                    <span>WordPress 4.6 or higher</span>\n                </li>\n						                <li>\n                    <span>Compatible up to:</span>\n                    <span>WordPress 5.2.x</span>\n                </li>\n						                <li>\n                    <span>Requires:</span>\n                    <span>WooCommerce 3.3.x or higher</span>\n                </li>\n						                <li>\n                    <span>Compatible up to:</span>\n                    <span>WooCommerce 3.6.x</span>\n                </li>\n			            <li>\n                <span>Minimum PHP version:</span>\n                <span>5.6</span>\n            </li>\n			                <li>\n                    <span>Version:</span>\n                    <span>1.0.3</span>\n                </li>\n						                <li>\n                    <span>Released:</span>\n                    <span>2019-05-29</span>\n                </li>\n						                <li>\n                    <span>100% WPML Compatible:</span>\n                    <span>yes</span>\n                </li>\n			            <li>\n                <span>Translation ready:</span>\n                <span>yes</span>\n            </li>\n			                <li>\n                    <span>Languages:</span>\n                    <span>English, Italian</span>\n                </li>\n			            <li>\n                <span>Support to:</span>\n                <span>\n						<br>All YITH plugins<br><br> All YITH themes                </span>\n            </li>\n			                <li>\n                    <span>GDPR Compliant:</span>\n                    <span>\n				    UNNECESSARY                </span>\n                </li>\n			        </ul>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"quick-info-actions\">\n		> View            <a href=\"https://docs.yithemes.com/yith-product-description-in-loop-for-woocommerce/\"\n               title=\"View documentation\"\n               target=\"_blank\">documentation</a>\n			or        <a href=\"#\" title=\"View changelog\"\n           data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#changelog\">changelog</a>\n    </div>\n\n	        <div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"changelog\" tabindex=\"-1\" role=\"dialog\" aria-labelledby=\"changelogLabel\"\n             aria-hidden=\"true\">\n            <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n                <div class=\"modal-content\">\n                    <div class=\"modal-body\">\n                        <button type=\"button\" class=\"close\" data-dismiss=\"modal\" aria-label=\"Close\"><span\n                                    aria-hidden=\"true\">&times;</span></button>\n						\n		\n		<h4>Version 1.0.3 - Released: May 29, 2019</h4>\n        <ul>\n           <li>New: Support to WordPress 5.2</li>\n		   <li>New: Option to enable the product description in every loop</li>\n		   <li>Update: Plugin Core</li>\n		   <li>Update: Italian language</li>\n        </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.2 - Released: May 02, 2019</h4>\n        <ul>\n            <li>New: Spanish language</li>\n			<li>New: Shortcodes can now be used inside descriptions</li>\n			<li>Update: Plugin Core</li>\n        </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.1 - Released: Apr 05, 2019</h4>\n        <ul>\n            <li>New: Support to WooCommerce 3.6</li>\n			<li>New: Dutch language files</li>\n			<li>Update: Plugin Core</li>\n			<li>Update: Language files</li>\n        </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.0 - Released: Mar 25, 2019</h4>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Initial Release</li>\n        </ul>\n		\n                        </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n	\n\n</div>\n\n    </div>\n	    </div>\n	\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;border: none\">WITH <span class=\"green\">YITH PRODUCT DESCRIPTION IN LOOP</span> YOU CAN:</h2>\n    <div class=\"row border\">\n		<br />\n    <div class=\"cols col-lg-6 \">\n		\n    <div class=\"image_title\">\n		            <h2>\n				Add a short and custom product description            </